{"word":"H4945 - מַשְׁקֶה - mashqeh - mash-keh' - Butler","slug":"H4945","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">מַשְׁקֶה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>mashqeh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>mash-keh'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Butler"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DE;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05E7;&#x05D4; - mashqeh</b> - <i>mash-keh'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H8248\">H8248</a>; properly <i>causing to drink</i>, that is, a <i>butler</i>; by implication (intransitively) <i>drink</i> (itself); figuratively a <i>well watered</i> region: - butler (-ship), cupbearer, drink (-ing), fat pasture, watered."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H8248\">H8248</a>, <a href=\"#/H8249\">H8249</a>, <a href=\"#/H8250\">H8250</a>, <a href=\"#/H8268\">H8268</a>"}]}